parameters:
Thug Henchman: At least... make it so he doesn't suffer
anymore... Ugh... Please, put my big bro out of his misery,
I beg you... uuu...
Henchman: Miss... what about the boss...?
I couldn't do it...
Henchman: No way...

Indeed, as you say, ensuring he doesn't suffer might be an
act of mercy.

But I couldn't bring myself to believe that was the right
thing to do...

Henchman: It's too much to see the boss turned into such a
state...

Indeed, the result that has befallen him is unbearable to
witness.
But just the same, we mustn't give up hope.

If magic experiments have caused this, then perhaps magic
could also be the key to restoring his original form, might
it not?

Henchman: But... until we find a way, the boss will remain
like that?!
You! You must be the one to believe in him!!

Is the man you so deeply trust really such a weakling? No,
that can't be right!!!

If you care about him, then you must believe! Believe in his
strength! In his tenacity to survive until now!! And in a
future where you can laugh together as comrades once more!!!
Henchman: Ugh! Uuuuuh...!!

It's true, you may be villains! But this is something that
cannot be allowed! Don't succumb to misfortune! Don't go
with the flow so easily! Choose to live on, no matter how
dirty it gets!
Just as you have survived together with him until now!

Henchman: Uuuuh...!! That's right...! The boss was dirtier
and tougher than anyone...! And yet, what was I
thinking...!!

You're not at fault. Your feelings for him were just too
strong, that's all.
Henchman: But... how do we find a way to turn the boss back?

Don't worry. Who do you think I am? I'm Reisha, a knight
from the royal capital Near Lake. I'll lend you my strength.
If we scour the capital and that's not enough, then we'll
search beyond our borders.

Once his case is resolved, you all will properly atone for
your crimes. Once your atonement is complete, call on me
again. Let's work together to make this country better!

Henchman: Ughuuu! I'm sorry...! So sorry...!! Uuuuhhh!!
Uuuuuuhhh...!!
chap04_02
chap04_02
Henchman: My bad, miss. You've given me encouragement.
Failed Boss: Fushuru... fushufushu...

Henchman: Thanks for bringing the boss here too. He slipped
right through the gap in the door. Never seen a door pass
like that. Even in this body, there are some perks, huh!
Ah! As expected of your boss!

Henchman: It's the least we can do. This was our prized
possession, but we want you to have it!

I appreciate it. I will put an end to the source of this
calamity in this facility. I promise to do my utmost to
prevent any further victims.

Just hold on here a little longer so that no one else finds
you.

Henchman: Yeah, we'll do that. We'll be in your care when we
get out. And again for a little while after everything is
resolved. And that time, the boss will be with us too.

Henchman: I won't ask what you're doing here, miss, but I'll
be praying for your safety and for your wishes to come
true...!!
Henchman: Sorry for making you do the tough stuff...

Henchman: This ain't much, but it's a token of my gratitude.
Please, take it.

...I will put an end to the source of this facility's
calamities. I promise to do my utmost to prevent any further
sacrifices.

I don't believe villains belong here, but please, just stay
put for a little while longer.

Henchman: Yeah, I'll do that. Once I'm out, I'll atone for
my sins. I'll be in your care then.

Henchman: I won't ask what you're here for, miss, but I'll
pray for just a bit longer that at least your wishes come
true...
Returning to the Memory Room.

Would you like to overwrite the event's outcome with the
current state? (This will affect the ending's branching.)
Yes
No
